- The integer array parameter `nums` must not be null.
- The length of the integer array parameter `nums` is greater than or equal to 3 and is less than or equal to 100000.
- All values in the integer array parameter `nums` are greater than or equal to 1 and are less than or equal to 1000000.
- The long result is the maximum value over all triplets of indices (i, j, k) such that i < j < k where the value of a triplet of indices (i, j, k) is equal to (nums[i] - nums[j]) * nums[k].
- If all triplets have a negative value, the long result is equal to 0.